							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/mazinsaleem/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/11/mazin-saleem-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Mazin Saleem" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/mazinsaleem/">Mazin Saleem</a></h6>
										Mazin Saleem is a writer from the UK. His first novel, <em>The Prick</em>, came out in 2019 with Open Pen, with a follow-up, <em>The Pricklet</em>, in 2021. He is a regular book and film critic, published in Strange Horizons, The Tribune, Film Cred, Little Atoms, and more. His short fiction has been published in 3AM Magazine, Litro Magazine, Minor Lits, and The Mays, and his substack <em>Artless</em> can be found at https://mazinsaleem.substack.com.																				<div class="website">
			    							<i class="fa fa-link"></i>
				    						<a href="https://mazinsaleem.substack.com" target="_blank" class="external">https://mazinsaleem.substack.com</a>
				    					</div>
				    														</div>
